## Format

Allowed values, examples, other constraints:
YYYY, YYYY-MM-DD, YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ssTZD or any other format or level of granularity described in W3CDTF. Use RKMS-ISO8601 standard for depicting date ranges.
Example: 2004-03-02/2005-06-02.
Years before 0000 must be prefixed with a - sign, e.g., -0054 to indicate 55 BC.



## Transforming

- Collected
    Description: The date or date range in which the resource content was collected.

    Usage Notes: To indicate precise or particular timeframes in which research was conducted.

- Coverage
    Description: The date or date range that the resource content applies to, describes, or covers.

    Usage Notes: To indicate the temporal coverage of the resource, use Coverage. This may be different from Collected.

